@chrismattmann Usage of env variable in unix/mac/linux is such that, it sets some environment variable and then run command. Ref. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Env
On windows, there is no exact alternative to do that. To workaround on windows, we execute 'set' command to set an environment variable and then execute another command in same environment. 
To achieve that, I switched to arraylist so that for Windows, I can delete command string "env" and its argument and pass rest of the commands as is.

